# MCP And Tooling

- Use read-only or discovery-first MCP servers by default.
- Keep project-scoped MCP config separate from user-level config.
- Scope filesystem, browser, memory, database, cache, and GitHub MCP access to the current app only.
- Do not mount sibling app directories, the parent template repo, home directories, or global mutable stores by default.
- If an MCP fails, note it once and continue with repo context unless the task truly depends on it.
